# CMS CRUD Form UI Pattern

Use this layout for **create/edit** pages (Articles and Prices are the reference). Future CRUD modules must follow the same pattern.

## Layout

- Page shell: `CmsPageShell` (glass) with sticky header actions
- Nested cards: **`SolidSurface`** — never nest `GlassSurface` inside the page shell for form sections
- Grid: main column + sticky-friendly aside (`xl:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_18rem|20rem]`)

## Shared primitives (`components/shared/`)

| Component | Use |
|-----------|-----|
| `CmsFormSectionHeading` | Section title + SF icon + accent color |
| `CmsFormFieldGroup` | Nested group inside a card (`bg-muted/50`, **no border**) |
| `CmsFormInfoPanel` | Created / updated / slug + unsaved-changes notice |
| `CmsFormDangerZone` | Destructive delete card (edit only) |
| Accents / icons | `config/form-ui.ts` + `cms-form-section-icons.tsx` |

Domain wrappers (e.g. `ArticleFormInfoPanel`, `PriceFormDangerZone`) only supply copy and dates — do not duplicate the visual pattern.

## Required sections

1. **Header** — Back link; create: plain title; edit: muted mode label + **entity name** accent
2. **Main** — One or more `SolidSurface` cards with section headings (content / media / etc.)
3. **Aside — Information** — metadata + dirty sections (amber) via `get*FormChangedSections` in `lib/{domain}/form-changes.ts`
4. **Aside — Publication / domain panels** — status and related fields
5. **Aside — Danger zone** — edit mode only

## Dirty tracking

- `useForm` `isDirty` + `get*FormChangedSections(baseline, watched)`
- After successful **update**, call `reset(values)` so the info panel clears
- Business logic stays in `lib/` — not in components

## Do / Don't

- ✅ `SolidSurface` for form cards; English UI copy
- ✅ One file = one component; share primitives instead of copying price/article markup
- ❌ Nested glass cards, colored left borders on field groups, or reinventing section headings
- ❌ Put created/updated only in Publication — prefer the Information panel
